cs.NI, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper discusses the feasibility of using Information-centric Networking (ICN) as a candidate network architecture for 5G, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and architecture (cs.AR). The paper also mentions the use of Network Function Virtualization (NFV) and Software Defined Networking (SDN), which are topics related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the provision of mobility-as-a-service (MaaS), which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
